full_text: Screened by NARA, 7/13/2023 U.S. Department of Justice OMB #1115-0052 Immigration and Naturalization Service Notice of Naturalization Oath Ceremony Naturalization and Citizenship Branch File or A # 300 NORTH LOS ANGELES STREET Date LOS ANGELES, CA 90012 You are hereby notified to appear for a Naturalization Oath Ceremony at the DATE, TIME AND PLACE SHOWN BELOW. Date 01/25/1999 ISAREL MARTINEZ-CRUZ Time 8:30 AM S BRONSON AVE Place You must bring the following with you: This letter, with ALL of the QUESTIONS ON THE REVERSE side answered in ink or on a typewriter. Alien Registration Card. Reentry Permit or Refugee Travel Document. Any immigration documents you may have. DY If the naturalization application is ON BEHALF OF YOUR CHILD (children), BRING your CHILD (children). 225 If you cannot come to this ceremony, return this notice immediately and state why you cannot appear. In such case, please use the return address in the extreme upper left hand corner of this letter. You will be sent another notice of ceremony at a later date. You must appear at an oath ceremony to complete the naturalization process. Form N-445A (Rev. 5/23/94)Y IMPORTANT - PLEASE SEE REVERSE
